Author: A Google User
Subject: Excellent
Body: For those complaining that it doesn't show certain USB devices (like with the Samsung Galaxy Tab), that's actually a bug within the Samsung kernel not firing intents for some HID devices!! If you click the linux tab you should be able to see all devices even if they are not detected by the android API.  If it still doesn't work the problem may be your USB cable (it has to be an OTG Host cable), and if that still isn't the problem it could be you're not on honeycomb 3.1+. Worked well for me.
